This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Filed: Original Transcript of Preliminary Hearing ( 12 pages) commencing 10-14-2022 by Debra A. Wisniewski.

Defendant Darious Marshawn Labarge appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Thomas Evangelos Harris appeared by video for Darious Marshawn Labarge.  Prosecuting attorney Thomas Hasle in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Court took judicial notice of Kenosha County case 20CF686. Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer Z. Szalacinski. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 02.
Scheduling conference scheduled for November 21, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Darious Marshawn Labarge not in court, in custody in HOC.  Attorney Thomas Harris appeared by video for Darious Marshawn Labarge. Prosecuting attorney Nate Kristian McClure in court in person for the State of Wisconsin. 

Case is set for a Status Of Counsel. Defense Counsel has been appointed. Defense Counsel requests a date for a Preliminary Hearing. Case is adjourned. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 14, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed: Attorney Thomas Harris

Defendant Darious Marshawn Labarge not in court, in custody in HOC.  Prosecuting attorney Abby Rockendorf appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case is set for a Preliminary Hearing. SPD has not appointed counsel. Case is adjourned. Court orders case adjourned for CAUSE for a Status of Counsel.
Status conference scheduled for September 23, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed: OSPD Appointment of Counsel Report

Defendant Darious Marshawn Labarge not in court, defendant in custody.  Gregg Herman appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a preliminray hearing. States witness is present. SPD has not appointed counsel. State requests that this matter be set for a State V. Lee hearing or status; denied. Court ordered case adjourned for CAUSE for a Preliminary Hearing in Preliminary Hearing Court, Room 146 of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 2, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Darious Marshawn Labarge in court with attorney Maryann Corea.  Defendant Darious Marshawn Labarge in custody.  Claire Louise Starling appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Darious Marshawn Labarge appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 02.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor count 4.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4). 
This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea
